    dc:date "2023" ;
    dc:title "Additions to Peroneutypa (Diatrypaceae, Xylariales): Introducing P. nayariophyti sp. nov. and new host associations of P. scoparia from northern Thailand" ;
    fabio:hasPart <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10012410>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10012412>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10012406> ;
    a fabio:JournalArticle .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10012410>
    dc:description "FIGURE 3. Peroneutypa nayariophyti (MFLU 23-0077, holotype). aAppearance of ascostromata on Nayariophyton zizyphifolium woody litter. b Upper view of the cross-section of ascostromata. c Cross section of ascostromata (arrowed). d, e Appearance of ascomata with a long neck on the substrate. f Peridium. g Paraphyses. h–m Asci. n–r Ascospores. s Germinated spore. t, u Culture characteristics on PDA from front and reverse. Scale bars: a = 1 mm, b–d = 500 μm, e = 200 μm, f = 50 μm, g–m, r, s = 10 μm, n–q = 5 μm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10012410/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10012412>
    dc:description "FIGURE 4. Peroneutypa scoparia (MFLU 23-0079, new host record). a Appearance of ascomata on Dalbergia cana woody litter. b, c Close up of ascomata on host substrate. d Vertical section through ascomata. e Cross-section of peridium. f Ostiol canal. g Paraphyses. h–m Asci. n–r Ascospores. s Germinated spore. t, u Culture characteristics on PDA from the front and reverse. Scale bars: a = 1 mm, b, c = 500 μm, d = 200 μm, g = 50 μm, e, f, h–j, l, s = 20 μm, k, m, r = 10 μm, n–q = 5 μm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10012412/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10012406>
    dc:description "FIGURE 1. Maximum likelihood tree from combined ITS and tub2 sequence data.Bootstrap support values ≥ 60% and Bayesian posterior probabilities ≥ 0.90 are indicated at the branches. The tree is rooted with Xylaria polysporicola (FCATAS848) and X. hypoxylon (CBS 122620). The taxa originating from this study are shown in blue. Type species are in bold." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10012406/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

